    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{5t^{2}+9t+4}{-t+5-6t^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{5t+4}{6t-5}, t\ne -1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{5t^{2}+9t+4}{-t+5-6t^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{\left(5t+4\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}}{{-6t^{2}-t+5}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(5t+4\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}}{{-\left(6t^{2}+t-5\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(5t+4\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}}{{-\left(6t-5\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{5t+4}{6t-5}, t\ne -1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t+1</m> was crossed out, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne -1</m>.</p>
</solution>
